olive oil
2 potato
2 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 tsp soy sauce
1 stalk celery
1 packet Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 tsp sesame oil
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet parsley

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a large bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken and toss to coat.
• When the potato has 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, then add sweet chilli sauce and the soy sauce, turning chicken to coat.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery.
• In a second medium bowl, combine slaw mix, celery, mayonnaise, the sesame oil and a drizzle of vinegar. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help toss the slaw.

• Slice the chicken.
• Divide sweet soy-glazed chicken, celery slaw and roast potato chunks between plates.
• Tear over parsley leaves to serve. Enjoy!